1. Create a Firebase Project
Visit Firebase Console.
Click on Add Project and follow the instructions.
Choose a project name (e.g., Taskify) and select Google Analytics settings.


2. Integrate Firebase with Flutter
Add Firebase SDK to your Flutter project:
Open pubspec.yaml and add dependencies:
yaml
dependencies:
  firebase_core: latest_version
  firebase_auth: latest_version
  cloud_firestore: latest_version
Run flutter pub get to install the dependencies.
Set up Firebase for Android:
Download google-services.json from Firebase Console.
Place it in the android/app directory.
Set up Firebase for iOS:
Download GoogleService-Info.plist.
Place it in the ios/Runner directory.
Ensure iOS platform version is at least 10.0 in pubspec.yaml.


3. Enable Firebase Authentication
In Firebase Console, go to Authentication → Get Started.
Enable sign-in methods (e.g., Email/Password, Google, etc.).


4. Set Up Firebase Firestore
In Firebase Console, go to Firestore Database → Create Database.
Choose test mode (for development).
Create collections (e.g., tasks, users) and set up the document structure based on your app's requirements.
